  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Supporting Evidence-Based and Accountable Humanitarian Service Provision to Conflict-Affected Populations through the Implementation of the Displacement Tracking Matrix (DTM) in the Far-North and North-West, South-West Regions of Cameroon</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The humanitarian response in Cameroon relies significantly on the regular collection, analysis and dissemination of displacement data shared through IOMs Displacement Tracking Matrix(DTM) which has been active in the Far-North since 2015 and was activated in the South-West and North-West regions at the end of 2018. Under this Action, IOM plans to continue providing the humanitarian community with information on displacement trends and most pressing sectoral needs of the conflict-affected populations in these regions. The role of DTM in supporting evidence-based and accountable service provision by humanitarian partners in Cameroon makes its continued implementation in 2020 a priority.</narrative>
  </description>
